steps.description:
The OPA plugin was implemented in PR apache/apisix#5734. To use it, configure the `opa` plugin on your APISIX route with the policy URI and request/response body handling options.
```yaml
# Example: Enable OPA plugin on an APISIX route
curl http://127.0.0.1:9180/apisix/admin/routes/1 \
  -H 'X-API-KEY: your-api-key' -X PUT -d '
{
  "uri": "/get",
  "plugins": {
    "opa": {
      "host": "http://opa-service:8181",
      "policy": "example/allow",
      "with_route": true,
      "with_consumer": true
    }
  },
  "upstream": {
    "type": "roundrobin",
    "nodes": {
      "httpbin.org:80": 1
    }
  }
}'
```

